  "original_title": "\u0d8b\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0db8\u0db1\u0dba \u0dc3\u0db8\u0d9c \u0dc3\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Theft increases with inflation",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to police sources, food theft has almost doubled in the country due to hyperinflation.",
        "It is said that the theft of food items from plantations has increased a lot and although many cases have been reported to the police, it is also known that information has not been submitted in the form of formal complaints.",
        "Also, thousands of cases of theft of food items from various business places including supermarkets have been reported from various parts of the island recently, according to the police headquarters.",
        "A senior police officer said that there seems to be an increase in theft of food items from shops.",
        "Also, several cases of theft of cooked food items (such as rice pots) were reported in recent days.",
        "A study conducted by the University of Peradeniya recently revealed that the number of families who eat one or at most two meals instead of three meals has increased to ten lakh due to the inflationary situation."
      ],
